### Is your feature request related to a problem? Please describe the problem.

Hi, I'm using the RevalidatingServerAuthenticationStateProvider in my Blazor server app - WORKS GREAT

ValidateAuthenticationStateAsync  is called every 5 minutes , which refreshes all circuits appropriately so there is no risk of a user having their role changed but still having access long after.

HOWEVER I am wondering, is there a way to manually trigger the ValidateAuthenticationStateAsync logic?

When I try to do it manually by creating a method to call it, it works for the current circuit, but does not update the other circuits.  However, if I wait for the interval, then all other circuits are updated.  Any ideas?

```csharp
  protected override TimeSpan RevalidationInterval => TimeSpan.FromSeconds(300);
    protected override  async Task<bool> ValidateAuthenticationStateAsync(AuthenticationState authenticationState, CancellationToken cancellationToken)
    {
        var user = authenticationState.User;
        if (user.Identity.IsAuthenticated)
        {
            var id = user.FindFirst(ClaimTypes.NameIdentifier)?.Value;
            if (id != null)
            {
               
                var _context = await dbFactory.CreateDbContextAsync(cancellationToken);
                var dbUser = await _context.Users.FirstOrDefaultAsync(u => u.Auth0Id == id, cancellationToken);

                // guart clause
                if (dbUser == null) return false;

                var identity = (ClaimsIdentity)user.Identity;
               
                var dbRole = dbUser.Role.ToString();

                var claims = identity.Claims.Where(_ => _.Type == ClaimTypes.Role).ToList();

                //remove claims that came from auth0 -no longer needed as we disabled it in auth0
                foreach (var claim in claims)
                {
                    identity.RemoveClaim(claim);
                }

      
                identity.AddClaim(new Claim(identity.RoleClaimType, dbRole));

                var newPrincipal = new ClaimsPrincipal(identity);
                var newAuthState = new AuthenticationState(newPrincipal);

       
                NotifyAuthenticationStateChanged(Task.FromResult(newAuthState));
       
                return true;
            }
        }
        return false;
    }
```

### Describe the solution you'd like

a method to manually trigger it, which I will use if I change the roles in the DB

